  "description": {
    "en": {
      "provenance": "imported",
      "value": "Child Poverty:Output 1:1.1Capacitate local governments and wards to undertake eligibility mapping, to conduct registration camps, open bank accounts and build awareness on social protection schemes (registration process, banking payments, renewal process) through different means of communication.1.2.Support local government to conduct activities that promote transparency and accountability of social protection programmes.1.3.Support province level governments to increase awareness with local governments and communities on social protection schemes, especially new schemes.   Output 2:2.1.Orient local governments, health facilities and communities on the Child Grant and facilitate access to the scheme.2.2.Capacity building of facilitators to deliver the parenting programme for parents/caregivers receiving the Child Grant.2.3.Build evidence on the impact of the Child Grant plus initiative and negotiate with province and federal government to scale this up. Output 3:3.1  Support 10 local governments and provinces to develop a coherent social protection policy and related interventions.3.2  Pilot Shock Responsive Social Protection (SRSP) in a few selected municipalities.3.3  Support the Social Protection Civil Society Network (SPCSN) to actively engage in promoting inclusive social protection in Nepal."
    },
    "ne": null
  },
